  "text": "In course of metastasis, cancer was spread beyond the place of origin into the other parts of body. Recurrence and metastasis of breast cancer after initial diagnosis and treatment are one of the major challenges for current therapeutic methods [CITATION_1] . Prevention of metastasis is very crucial for success of breast cancer therapy and survival of patients after diagnosis and treatment. Here, we investigated the migration inhibition potential of AEEA and results suggested that it has potentially inhibited the migration of breast cancer cell lines.",
